Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Neck and oval handle. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Clay near fine pink-buff; white inclusions.
Curator's comments: Name Euanor. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 041.29. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1155)
